Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
replace_proto_model(25.10)                          replace_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       replace_proto_model  -  Converts flexmodel netlist back to the original
       full netlist  with  changes  at  the  partition  block  level  whenever
       feedthrough insertion step is needed in the flow

Syntax
        replace_proto_model

       [-help]

       [-out_dir <string] >

       [-ptn_dir <string>]

       [-module_model_tag <string> -full_module_model_tag<string>]

       Converts  flexmodel  netlist  back  to  the  original full netlist with
       changes at the partition block  level  whenever  feedthrough  insertion
       step  is  needed  in the flow. You can use this command after using the
       savePartition command. This command saves a directory under each parti-
       tion directory with the  default  name  <designName>_proto_full.enc.dat
       and you need to use this DB for block implementation.

       To use this command in a FlexModel based partition flow:

              * Import a full chip FlexModel netlist design.

              * Floorplan the design.

              * Run the following commands to analyze the floorplan.

                * place_design

                * earlyGlobalRoute

                * timeDesign -proto

                * load_timing_debug_report -proto

              * Do feedthrough insertion .

              * Do pin assignment

              * Optionally optimize the design.

              * Budget the timing for blocks using the deriveTimingBudget com-
                mand.

              * Partition the design using the partition command.

              * Save  the  partition  using  savePartition  -dir  $ptnDir (for
                placement and pin locations copy)

              * replace_proto_model -ptn_dir $ptnDir -outdir $ptnDir

       Note: The replace_proto_model command only supports the netlist changes
       caused by feedthrough insertion, so replace_proto_model will  have  is-
       sues  if there is some netlist change issued by other commands such as-
       createLogicHierarchy before calling replace_proto_model. This is a lim-
       itation for the replace_proto_model command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each replace_proto_model parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man replace_proto_model.

       -full_module_model_tag< string>
              Specifies  the  module  model  tag for the original full netlist
              that is used in the iHDB directory structure for saving the full
              hierarchical DB (output) after eco.

              Note: The -full_module_model_tag and  -module_model_tag  parame-
              ters  are  part  of  the Integrated Hierarchical Database (iHDB)
              flow and are used by the replace_proto_model command to  convert
              the  FlexModel  netlist back to the original full netlist in the
              iHDB directory structure. Before  using  these  parameters,  you
              must  set  the  default central directory name (set_module_model
              -default_dir <default_model_data_directory> ) where  the  module
              models data will be saved/loaded.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -module_model_tag <string>
              Specifies  the module model tag for the hierarchical DB (input).
              This module model tag is used  in  the  Integrated  Hierarchical
              Database flow.

              Note:  The -full_module_model_tag and  -module_model_tag parame-
              ters are part  of  the  iHDB  flow  and  are  used  by  the  re-
              place_proto_model  command to convert the FlexModel netlist back
              to the original full netlist in the  iHDB  directory  structure.
              Before  using these parameters, you must set the default central
              directory    name    (set_module_model     -default_dir     <de-
              fault_model_data_directory>  ) where the module models data will
              be saved/loaded.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -out_dir <string>
              Specifies the directory to save post ECO full top/block  netlist
              partition data.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -ptn_dir <string>
              Specifies the partition directory for original full netlist.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following command will read the FlexModel data with tag name "ptn"
       as input, and dump the original full netlist with tag  name  "full"  in
       the iHDB directory structure.

       replace_proto_mode  -module_model_tag ptn -full_module_model_tag full

